	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[1.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I have my feelings posted here on the issue of why clerics suck, even though I am a cleric myself.<br><br>1. We are overworked, because nobody else in the classes has "good" healing, though shamans, paladins, and druids can heal too. In simple terms, we are overworked, underpaid, rezzing/healing/buffing machines, that according to others "should work 24/7" with no pay.... we are kind and heal and buff people, but we don't get any $$$ for it...<br><br>2. All our quests suck, and there HASN'T been a low-level quest that I've seen.<br><br>3. We have to go and Buy all our freaking armor, see #2 for reason.<br><br>4. We are the poorest of newbies... like I said, we have few quests and don't get donations for casting low level spells... Druids and shammys get money for SoW, why can't we get any money for our spells, dammit?!? See Reason #1!<br><br>Hope you agree with me. Post me replies on your agreement/disagreement/indifference with these issues.<br><br><br>&nbsp;<br>Chriskaballa<br>11th level cleric<br>The Nameless</td></tr>
