	   <tr><td colspan=2>I hardly agree that clerics suck, and I really haven't had any of the problems you seem to describe.  <br>1.  I don't see being the best type of healer in the game as overworked.  In many cases I've helped restore HP for people who freely give donations, enchanters who give clarity, and shamans/druids who give SoW.  That, on top of being one of the best buffing classes in the game, makes you great to group with.  If that weren't enough, those same skills make you a great help when Plvling someone for money!<br>2. I'll admit that the Temple of Ro quests are hard, and the armor isn't the best, but there are a bunch of other things that are great for clerics that you can hunt or buy (burnyai legion gi, BS tunic, etc.) And low lvl quests, there are plenty of, not to mention that you don't have to stick to your own Class's quests especially at lower lvls.<br>3. AT very low lvls I made myself PW, then went and hunted ringmail.  I easily made money by saving up and hunting in good locations.  I would much rather have to buy better armor than not be able to wear it at all (druids, shamans, etc)<br>4.  Ahem*  RESSURECTION I know that you don't get this till much later, but Druids and Wizzys don't start raking in the cash till lvl 29 either.  And how can you compare distance traveling to hours and hours saved by exp rezzes?  BTW, how hard is it really to find a free SoW?<br>I agree with Bolitho, I don't see how you could have ended up at this idea that clerics suck.<br>Gedran<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
